<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="689" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.77/84.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs says that American forces were landed at
                            Puerto Cortés this morning; all were reembarked but one, who is
                            stationed in the office of the superintendent of the railroad. A
                            communication was quoted from the American Vice Consul at that port
                            advising the Minister for Foreign Affairs that the commander of the
                            American war vessel had taken possession of the railroad pending
                            instructions. Firm but courteous protest was made by the Minister.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
